The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Feb. 27: Crisils board of directors has approved the merger of Crisil Research and Information Services, Crisil Properties and Global Data Services of India with the company. After assessment of the merits of restructuring the Indian operations, the board has also approved the scheme incorporating the proposed arrangement for the merger.

 New Delhi, Feb. 27: The countrys FDI inflow shot up nearly six-fold in December 2006 to touch $2.04 billion from $350 million in the same month of the previous year. This is the highest-ever FDI inflow in a single month, Kamal Nath said. 

 Mumbai, Feb. 27: Marico shareholders have given their nod to a stock split exercise. This would result in the sub-division of 6.09 crore equity shares of nominal value of Rs 10 each into 60.90 crore equity shares of nominal value of Re 1 each. 

 Stockholm, Feb. 27: Volvo has agreed to buy the road construction machinery business of US-based Ingersoll-Rand in a $1.3-billion cash deal.

 Mumbai, Feb. 27: JSW Steel today witnessed a block deal on the stock exchanges when close to 50 lakh shares were transacted at both the NSE and BSE. The total value of these deals stood at over Rs 235 crore. 

